values:
An email I sent to the web site's administrator:

I recently read a review of a local bake shop and I had a REAL problem with what the reviewer said. People are entitled to their own opinions and what reviewers have to say about the food and about the quality of the service, but lobbing insults about the weight/size of the staff should be hardly acceptable. I doubt if you'd accept criticisms from reviewers that had a problem with staff being black, Asian, or Jewish. This particular reviewer stated the following about the staff of The Sweetery Bake Shop in Cleveland, MS: "some big ole girls running a bake shop lol..."
REALLY?!?! My God, REALLY?! You permit your users to include such personally inflammatory hate speech into their reviews without providing a means for reporting INAPPROPRIATE comments? Not liking the food and saying so is fine, so are criticism of the service, decor, prices, but using your review to CALL THE STAFF FAT?!?!

How can your web site CONDONE AND ENDORSE that type of childish objectification of PEOPLE and not even provide a means for others to REPORT someone using their review as a means for PERSONAL INSULTS?

This isn't the only incident for this business. another reviewer stated "the staff looks like they eat more of the icing than they do cooking! "

Perhaps I should inform other hate groups and people with blatantly offensive things to say that urbanspoon.com offers it members the opportunity to insult and degrade PEOPLE with complete impunity, so long as they mention the restaurant's food or prices while the do it.

I would like to request that your site put in place a means of reporting offensive posts and comments and I would also request that users that can't live with the restriction of not not PERSONALLY INSULTING PEOPLE ON THE BASIS OF HOW THEY LOOK, not be allowed to review restaurants here.

For the past three months I'd been dating Heather Henderson. She'd had chronic bronchitis for about 2 months. Her doctor initially diagnosed it as allergies, she could never breathe well during this time. It got so bad that her mom MADE her go to the emergency room a few days ago. Last night she was at their place and woke her mom up and told her she couldn't breathe. She coded on the way to the hospital, they revived her there and she passed away at 3:15. Her sister said they think it was a pulmonary embolism. Trying to let people know. I am having a hard time with it, but friends are helping. please keep her family, friends, and I in your prayers. If you hear from anyone that wants to know, the visitation will be tomorrow at the Wilson and Knight funeral Home in Greenwood, MS from 5-7 pm and the funeral Monday at 11:00 starting at the funeral home. I miss her so much. http://www.geoffreylatham.com/Heather.jpg http://www.geoffreylatham.com/heatherforever.jpg

Saturday night I had a little fender bender at a gas station in Senetobia. Bad luck. things happen. Later after I was driving through Batesville (Eric Perry and Andrew Owen in the car with me) I hit a deer on Hwy 6 west. ($5475.00 estimate from the collision). Pictures AND video are available on myspace, facebook, and youtube. So as if the first run in with mother nature wasn't enough... I am running this game of vampire down the street when mom calls me and says that she got scared half to death because she heard a loud noise and came to find the attic stairs door all the way down in the hallway. Neither of us could imagine what it might be so I said if it happens again call me back. So, I come home late after my game and start getting ready for bed and I notice a couple of things in my room are askew Nothing is missing; just some stuff on the floor moved around. I get paranoid and start looking around with a flashlight. I notice a small moisture stain on the rug beside my bed and a box that is usually under my bed poking out a little so I psyche myself up and lift up the foot of my bed just high enough to see under. It takes me several seconds to realize what it is I am looking at and then BLAM! It comes into focus and there in the corner of my room curled up under my box springs is the biggest fucking possum I have EVER seen! I went back to Klint's house down the street and he and Chris Hartfield (Both sinfonians) helped me retrieve it after a long and bloody conflict. It wouldn't "play possum" so we subdued it with a baseball bat and snared it with an extension cord lasso. They wailed on that damn thing like Rodney King and it still freakin' survived!!! We took it to the curb and let it go.

I used to be fun at parties.
I used to be witty and charming, bawdy and brazen
I used to be charismatic and jubilant.
People would hang on my every word.
The world would listen when I spoke.
All within earshot would erupt with riotous laughter when my stories reached their climax or my anecdote came to their conclusion.
I am 0old and sad. I revile and puzzle those around me. 
I have not just grown up; I have become old and tragic.
My presence is an echo of an extinct breed.
I am a fossil and my good time ends with the silence of me driving home alone

One minute till six AM and I have evaded sleep for the past 12 hours due to a terminal lack of motivation to rest. Usually laziness is its own reward but now I can't seem to bring myself to even be lethargic. My mind is a blurred cacophony of introspective horror and giddy dementia. A mental mayonnaise jar full of used engine oil, dirt, and water held together in a globulous emulsion of endomorphic chaos is the only metaphor I can construct to illustrate my psycho-mental, spiritual-ideological, emotional-intellectual muck. I am unkempt, unwashed, disheveled, crude smelling, savage looking, and in all other ways perceptible by the human imagination uncivilized. Yet, I feel oddly contented and appreciative of this state of being, state of mind, and stage of development. It must be a stage of development, for without development there is stagnation and that which does not evolve becomes extinct and there is far too much kinetic karma at work for any signs of extinction. What would Thompson do? What hasn't he done? Only a man so misunderstood as he could possibly be called kindred and then only in the lack of understanding about him are we alike.  My grammar check chokes on the previous sentence. Can the imagination be bound, whipped, and made to conform to the limited grammatical mechanics of a computer program? Faulkner would write for days without punctuation. I suspect it is conspiracy by the technocratic elite to dumb down the masses by instilling the idea that stream of consciousness though and fluidic ideas are inherently wrong. 

     I think my problem is that I may have lost the weird. There was once a sense of adventure a true spirit of Gonzo that echoed within me and those like minded souls that glimpsed the madness that I have so closely skirted, but it has given way to pragmatism, ambition, calculated planning and worship of the banal. It never got weird enough for me. Not when those four black guys fucked the good sense and decency out of the carefree Asian nymph on my dorm room bed, not when I crawled bloody, muddy, soaking, half naked and almost barefoot, dripping with sticky brown beverage through the wee hours of the morning, not when we charged in with dogged determination to assault Aleshia's knee, steal Spot's cat, harass their houseguests with small bottles of liquor and gumball machine toys and certainly not when crazed on liquor and exhaustion I dawned an orange road cone as my crown and strode into traffic as a king into court, was it ever weird enough for me. Frank knew. He saw it in me. He could see the t-shirt that said I went to the brink of sanity and back and all I got was this lousy t-shirt. He had one to. No, he had more than one but he took the express train there. I walked slowly and deliberately and peered in to the wild amorphous mass that churned below and said hello to the sirens that were calling me to leap in. I did not leap. Now, I have walked so far back that I can no longer hear the siren's call or hear the waves of insanity as they crash upon the rocky shores of rationality.

I do so miss the seaside.

The oysters were always fresh there and each always contained a pearl.

A long walk on the beach would do me good.

Perhaps this time, I may go for a swim.

the advertisements on myspace for TRUE.com or whatever it is are blatantly provocative.
They remind me of the sex that I am not having.
That makes me grit my teeth in frustration.
Gritting my teeth makes them hurt and reminds me that i need to floss more often.
Thinking about oral hygiene reminds me of the dentist and how expensive it is.
Expenses remind me that I am self - employed (which means unemployed but licensed to do things) and broke.
Being broke sucks and prevents me from going out and doing things.
Not being able to go and and do things means I stay at home.
When I stay at home i sit behind my computer the whole time and waste time at myspace
Wasting time at myspace forces me to notice ads for true.com
this is an endless cycle....
I have a fever... and the only prescription...is more cowbell!

I was up early this morning to see mom and dad off to Atlanta. They are taking one of my cousins to the Cordon Bleu Culinary school there for a parent's orientation dinner. Mom and dad are kind of sponsoring her to go there and study. At any rate, as I was sitting in the den in my bathrobe, mom mentioned that she'd brought home some picture albums from my grandmother's house. I started looking through them and I decided to scan the album. I then went on a quest to find other pictures that I wanted to preserve and began scanning them. I had a very emotional moment looking at friends family and records of the past. Mom and dad had already left and I was left here with the only thing breaking the silence the gentle hum of my scanner and "hallelujah" (I think it was Jeff Buckley). As I sat there looking into the faces of the past and listening to the half mournful half resplendent music I thought of Jacki and how much I want someday for her to be a part of my family and for me to be a part of her's. I looked up and stared at her picture on my wall and I was overcome with a sense of joy. I could feel my heart glow and I prayed and thanked God for her and all of the blessings he's gifted me with. Sometimes she makes my entire day without even saying a word to me. I love her.

Today is for cleaning and preparing to grill and play D&D.
I am now a licensed health insurance agent and soon I will probably be working with several companies enrolling people in Medicare part "C" or Medicare advantage plans. If any of my faithful readers have friends, family, or close acquaintances over 65 or that you know are on Medicare, I'd love for you to mention me to them and give me a referral once I start working. I've come to think that Medicare advantage plans are an excellent and cost effective type of coverage for those who are eligible. I wouldn't be doing it if I didn't think it was worthwhile and helpful to people.

My toes are healing nicely and there is no more pain. :)
I dinged 62 on my warcraft rogue.
I am broke but have some money coming in around the start of March.
D&D game is going well so far.
life is a blessing.

I signed up for a facebook account this morning, so all of YOU that have one as well, add me as a friend...
...or I shall THROW A PUPPY IN TO A WOODCHIPPER!



in other news...

I'm making Home-made Beef Jerky!!!

This is cured, jerky (REAL jerky) not "cooked" jerky. I sampled a piece a couple of hours ago and it was, imho, fnatastic; sweet, spicy, smokey, and with just the right amount of delayed heat! I think once the batch completely dries out it will be amazing. All the local folks are invited to sample while supplies last. If it works well, I may turn it into a regular endeavor. For those of you that watch Good Eats on the food network, my method is the one employed by Alton Brown.

I went to Octoberfest this weekend and performed my annual ritual of bratwurst and beer. I saw some old familiar faces. It was especially pleasant to bump into Katie Kent.

Aside from that, not much esle to speak of; still no job, though I am determined to muster myself back into looking more actively now that my sister's move and other things have sort of calmed down.

Well I suppose that is all for now. Ciao!

So, tonight I had real "put you to sleep surgery" for the first time. I was in the hospital by 4 and out by nine, but it was an aggravating ordeal. I had a perirectal abcess lanced and drained or in laymans terms, a big bubble of puss on my behind popped. From feeling of it before the surgeyry it was about the size of a medium sized peach. This si the second one I've had lanced but this was the first time i've ever been "put under" for anything. I literally almost freaked out in anesthesia. I was lying there with no glasses on my back (I HATE lying on my back) and i was just getting more and more irritated about the uncomfortable position and the fact that I couldn't stop coughing (I've had some sinus drainage and it was giving me fits)

finally they wheeled me into to the OR, sedated me did their thing and brought me out again (which seemed like sort of a shock at the time). Now I have to miss a couple days of school (which will prolly cost me a few hundred dollars because I have no more sick days left.) God KNOWS how much the surgery and meds will cost even AFTER insurance. And I have a few days of sits baths, bleeding, oozing, drainage, bandages and dressings to deal with. Woot. Dad said he would come get me so i could spend the time at home (it may not be the ideal place especially considering sleeping options, but at least I wouldn't be alone. A BIG thank you goes out to Chiclet and Julie who came to my rescue even at the expense of chiclet's poor car. and another thanks to Rick and Jennie who came to THEIR rescue because of Chiclet's car. Well, I suppose I will go back to bed and try to sleep more. Wish me luck and fast recovery. ciao.

Yes, it is an entry... shut yer mowth!

 

I have been feeling so unmotivated as of late. I have excessive tardies and excessive absences at work; I have a huge backlog of papers to grade and grades to record and put into new spreadsheets. I have lesson plans that need to be written. I need to get on the ball applying for new positions for the fall and I need to try and get things ready for Jacki coming down and eventually moving out of the Hickory Hood. I am paranoid in my apartment. I always check to see if the door is still locked once I walk back in and I scope out around the corner before coming back inside. Whenever I got o bed I take my wallet and keys in to the bedroom with me and lock the door when I sleep. I hate being influenced by fear. I need to get applications planted out, filled out, and sent out. I need to contact my awesome cool Aunts Liz and Carolyn and see about getting that furniture up here to my apartment, I need to get my taxes done, I need to get a new queen size bed, I need to find some way to motivate myself. I need to visit my doctor and get my prescriptions back on track. 
<lj-cut>
 

I have really begun to question whether education is the right profession for me. I can't seem to bridge the gulf of cultural schism between my students and myself. I can't get them to follow simple instructions because the majority of them have such a complete and total disdain for all forms of authority and very little sense of self improvement or a sense of repercussions for their actions. I don't know what else I might do that would afford me the type of schedule that I want, the type of money I'd like to make, and using the skills and knowledge that I possess. I sometimes think about those days when I felt God truly working in my life. I recall when full time ministry was what I knew I was destined for. Somewhere along the way, however I become disenfranchised with the worldly aspect of working within the church. I felt that I didn't have the people skills necessary and I was unwilling to try and develop them. Am I a slave to my own arrogance? Am I unwilling to try and live up to the expectations that society places upon a man called to serve? Peter, Paul, and all of other Christ's followers were rather unsavory characters and only later became the instruments that God would have them be.

 

Have I come full circle? And if so, how do I fly out of the weary sorrowful circle of life? How do I put off mortality and become divine? (To coin a phrase)

How do I persevere through the ravages of the cacophony of voices that make up an entire chorus of voices of doubt telling me to stop, give up, retreatturn back around and LOOK!

 

I keep telling myself if only. If only, she was here with me. If only I could save a little money. If Only I could find a way to make a difference. If only I could gain the motivation to fulfill the potential that both God and I know that I am capable of. If only I had the time, the energy, the willpower. And what of the artist? Where is my creative outlet? Where is my canvas? Where is the fire that used to burn within to fulfill that most Godlike emulation and bring forth form and wonder out of the simplest of components; out of nothingness? What is my message to the world? What is it that I want to share what is it that I have to say? How can my existence benefit and enlighten those around me and those to come after?

 

I feel that I am a performer. I need to be recognized, appreciated, applauded, and seen I all things and when my best efforts in all things fall upon deaf ears and are placed before blind uncaring eyes, it slowly kills that performer inside. I keep waiting for those intrinsic rewards that Teaching is supposed to bring; I keep waiting for the wisdom I have to share to be relevant and meaningful to anyone. I yearn to make an impact and influence someone but the waiting continues and all the insight I have I shout into the cave and hear not only a silence of reply, but even an absence of echo. My words and deeds do not even ring true unto myself. I pray that it is only because the cavern is deep and not that my voice is too small or my words to foolish to resound. 

 

            I must connect with my muse. For now I shall do my best to dig in and keep on keeping on. If nothing else persistence may be its own reward. My greatest victory may yet be to look back upon all that I have failed at and say confidently that I TRIED!

 

Mindless tedium! That is what my life feels like, though how could it be? There is so much going on. I sometimes feel like I'm on the outside of my own life looking in. My prophetic visions of my own future are incongruent with the circumstances of my life. There is a missing link in the future evolution of ME! Somewhere between now and then there is something climactic that must happen; some paradigm shift that must occur in order to bring about the metamorphosis from what I am to what I shall, should, could, can, might, ought to be!

 

I know when my alliteration starts to surface that I am slipping closer to the edge. Frank said that he could tell that I have skirted the edge at times and he is so correct in that summation. I have stood at the brink of the abyss and felt my weight pulling me forward and down, but fear and those tethers of the mundane have always pulled me back before I slipped, nay, DOVE into that tenebrous maelstrom. What lies at the bottom? If I fall shall I find light at the end of the rabbit hole? How deep does it go? Is this black hole a gravity that will crush me under the weight of its bleakness or shall I come out the other side enlightened and illuminated and transformed? Ascension or damnation, both, neither, who can answer but those who have gone before and who has gone before and lived tot ell the tale? 

 

Questions; this entry is full of questions and all the answers are waiting for me to discover too late to make the questions relevant for change.

My dichotomy once again reveals itself. I yearn for change and transition, but a change and transition into a greater stability. But dichotomy is what I am and it is the way of nature. The sun's rays give all life and yet they also take it away and bleach white our bones that lie within their warm embrace. I seek chaos in order to achieve a maintained stability to begat other types of chaos.

 

Woe's me. I must always do my best to trust God. I must have FAITH that "she doth follow thee" and to step out of the cave boldly into the light of day before looking back to embrace Eurydice. 

 

I need to reset. I need to rewind. I need to start fresh. I need to rise above. I need to focus and summon forth that hidden strength and drive that can allow me to do great things.

 

I also need to clean my apartment and do some laundry.

Sloth is the sweetest and most deadly of sins.

Goodnight, All. God Bless.

Well, Marshall is gone and my place is once more empty and quiet. I do so love having company. My place feels so much more like a home when someone else is here. When Melody stayed for a few days it was like home and with Marshall staying since Monday it has been such a warmer and more comfortable place to be. I feel truly alone when I am here with noting but the television and assorted appliances and other mechanical noises filling the silence that hangs in the air like a cloud. My cupboards are nearly bare, I have 60 bucks to last me 10 days. My life feels like I am living the same day over and over again. There is no excitement, no change, no sense of progression. The only changes I see happening are my finances dwindling, things wearing out, entropy chipping away at everything eve3n my health. I was rejuvenated for a while to see Marshall and getting to see him run some D&D inspired me again for my game. It made me yearn for days more simplistic than the ones of the present. We as creatures must bask in our pasts. We live in the present and it moves by so fast that to it is impossible to savor it within the blur, the future is unknown and never stable, but our memories are ours to relish in and the glory we once knew gives us strength to continue on.

I guess I'm being kind of pissy.

I am a lucky son of a bitch. I know that. My friends have showed me so and I know that it is the truth.

Anyhow... Marshall has a new Myspace, so go check it out.

I am going to see what I can scrounge up for supper. Goodnight all and God Bless.
